dataIdInfo.suppInfo: This dataset was built on and enhanced from a previous shapefile for watershed council boundaries. In 2011, all boundaries were reviewed and aligned with the most current, available data. OWEB project managers, watershed council coordinators and others were consulted to review existing data and asked to submit changes and or additions. Hard copy maps and/or shapefiles were submitted for changes that were needed. Using Hydrologic Unit Code boundaries (HUCs), in most cases, council boundaries were delineated in ArcMap 10.0 while referencing hard copy maps. The geographic features and source data used to delineate boundaries are noted in the defFeature and defFeatureNote attributes.

dataLineage.statement: This dataset has been updated and modified over time on an as needed basis. New watershed councils are continuing to be formed and changes to existing councils also occur. In 2011 the dataset was aligned with the Oregon Administrative Boundary Standard as applicable - paying particular focus to attribute data. Because council's have overlapping juristictional boundaries due to multiple local governments recognizing the formation of councils, this dataset is not able to meet the Edge Matching rules outlined in the Standard. In addition there are some areas of the state that, as of yet, have no established watershed council.
